modules.description: Provides functions to construct and manipulate linear and quadratic expressions, define constraints, and set objectives for optimization models. Works with variables, expressions, and constraints represented as algebraic structures. Enables integration with GLPK and Gurobi solvers by generating CPLEX LP files or direct calls.

Handles configuration and input parameters for GLPK solvers in JavaScript environments. Processes numeric arrays, sparse matrices, and constraint definitions for linear programming problems. Used to set solver tolerances, algorithm choices, and problem data before execution.
